      "lecture_id": "econometrics_mle_challenge_001",
      "text": "Maximum-Likelihood Estimation estimates an econometric model by maximizing the likelihood of the observed sample. The likelihood is viewed as a function of the model parameters with the sample held fixed.\n"
    },
    {
      "lecture_id": "statistics_mle_challenge_001",
      "text": "Maximum Likelihood Estimation selects parameter values that maximize the likelihood. The likelihood compares parameter values after the observed data are held fixed. An MLE estimator may be written as\n\n\\[\n\\widehat{\\theta}_{\\mathrm{MLE}} = \\operatorname*{arg\\,max}_{\\theta} L(\\theta;x).\n\\]\n"
    }
  ]
}
